walk through &&, ||, and !, then use the OR trick to fake a function default value the old-school way, back before ES6 gave us real defaults.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002Fjavascript-core-19-logical-operators-default-values","3",{"title":6,"description":700},false,"en\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-core-19-logical-operators-default-values",[698,710,711],"JavaScript Core","Operators, Types, and Grammar",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-core-19-logical-operators-default-values\u002F","F7sYiYzlGiO0waCsuyXR-L6cvSP-vGpGMcl9Hzxf6rg",{"newer":716,"older":720},{"url":717,"title":718,"date":719},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F05\u002Fjs-core-concepts-20-operators-types-grammar-exercises\u002F","JS Core Concepts (20): Operators, Types & Grammar — Practice Quiz","2020-07-05 21:42:59",{"url":721,"title":722,"date":723},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F07\u002F01\u002Fpixijs-v5-21-collision-boundary-03\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (21) - Collision Boundaries (3): Random Positions and Centering Text","2020-07-01 15:30:15",[725,730,735],{"url":726,"title":727,"date":728,"readingMinutes":729},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2026\u002F03\u002F10\u002Fweb-crypto-api-encryption-guide\u002F","No crypto Package, No Node.js — The Web Crypto API Does It All in the Browser","2026-03-10 09:45:08","9",{"url":731,"title":732,"date":733,"readingMinutes":734},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F08\u002Fjquery-why-it-declined\u002F","jQuery Was Once King — So Why Did It Fall Off?","2025-12-08 21:35:24","7",{"url":736,"title":737,"date":738,"readingMinutes":739},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F","What Are JavaScript Generator Functions (function*)? The Function You Can Pause and Resume","2025-12-05 13:40:31","5",1784087329178]